                    <h1>Picnics</h1>
                <p><p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><img width="402" align="right" height="291" alt="" src="/coopergarrod/up/editor/image/tasting%20room%20-%20picnic3.jpg" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: medium;">We</span></span><span style="font-size: medium;">'</span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: medium;">re just about the perfect picnic venue:&nbsp; 100-year-old Eucalyptus trees, riding arenas, and valley views.&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: medium;">So bring a picnic to enjoy with some of our wines!&nbsp;<br />
</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: medium;">Please observe our policies concerning our property and use of our picnic tables:&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<ul>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Picnic tables are for customer use only; if you do not intend to purchase tastings and/or wine, we ask that you enjoy your day at another location.</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">All tables are available both by <span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><a href="http://www.cgv.com/reservations">reservation</a></span></span></span></span> and first come/first-serve basis. Reservations for weekend days must be made by the Friday prior.&nbsp; </span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">On Sundays during the music season, we do not hold any tables after 1 PM, when music begins.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Groups of 8 or fewer may be seated on the upper plaza; groups of 9 or more will be in the lower picnic area.&nbsp; &nbsp;Not all large groups can be accommodated, and more advance notice is suggested.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Anyone consuming wine on our property must be able to prove that they are 21 years or older. &nbsp;Please have appropriate ID on hand at all times.</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">        Due to licensing and liability restrictions, we do not allow &quot;Outside Alcohol&quot; on our grounds. (&quot;Outside Alcohol&quot;        is defined as any alcoholic beverage not purchased from Cooper-Garrod on-site        the day of your visit.) </span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">No smoking.</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">        Children should remain under close parental supervision at all times. Our staff reserves        the right to ask that families depart the grounds if supervision does not meet our        standards.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Horses are privately owned; look and enjoy, but please do not pet or feed. &nbsp;(Please note: horses bite!) </span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Because of the presence of horses, please note we do not allow balloons, noise makers, streamers, pinatas, or candles/open flames to be used in our picnic area.</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">Pets should be on leash at all times, and must be people-friendly, dog-friendly, and, importantly, horse-friendly! &nbsp;If you are unsure about any of the above, we ask kindly for everyone's safety that the pet be left home. &nbsp;Our staff reserves the right to ask any owners and problem animals to depart the grounds.</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">We are happy to provide glasses for you to drink our delicious wine; please return to members of the Cooper-Garrod staff when finished! &nbsp;</span></span></li>
    <li><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">We cannot pour wine, or have guests anywhere on the premises, after our posted closing time.</span></span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">    </span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;">We have established these policies to ensure a pleasant, peaceful, and safe experience    for all our customers, and we thank you in advance for your compliance with the    above. </span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman;"><br />
</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
